The ANs membrane was prepared by a simple electrospinning method and an annealing process. X-ray diffraction (XRD) patterns of the prepared membrane suggest the formation of the hybrid phase of β-Al2O3 and β″-Al2O3 after annealing at 1250 °C (Fig. 2a). Since the β-Al2O3 and β″-Al2O3 phases have similar X-ray diffraction peaks, the relative amount of the β″-Al2O3 phase can be calculated using the major peak intensities of XRD patterns of the ANs membrane, as shown in Eq. (1)43.1fβ′′=100%−fβ=1−1.14Iβ1.14Iβ+Iβ′′×100%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
